stent_note":"Rejected Integration because behavior text binds correctness to creation timestamps from the filesystem; fake metadata would miss real precision/tie issues.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A file that is still being written to when the arrival event fires is not picked up for processing until writing is complete.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is a real race between OS file events and write completion/visibility. In-process mocks tend to model a clean completion point and can miss partial-read timing failures.","test_description":"With daemon running on a real directory, write a large file in chunks with delays (keeping stream open). Verify no processing starts until final close/settle condition, then assert processing occurs once with full content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
